# Betting Workspace — Global Rules

## Architecture
- Agent-driven pipeline: orchestrator calls individual scripts, delegates analysis to specialists.
- Database-first: `betting/data/betting.db` via `get_db()`. JSON/CSV/MD are secondary artifacts.
- Discovery: `src/bet/discovery/` — API-first for 5 core sports.
- Scripts produce data; agents interpret output and return structured verdicts.
- `pipeline_orchestrator.py` is BANNED — orchestrator mode IS the loop.

## Model & Hardware
- Agentic/thinking: Qwen3.6-27B Dense 8-bit via Rapid-MLX on localhost:8000.
- Thinking mode: ALWAYS ON (<think> blocks via qwen3 parser). NEVER use --no-thinking.
- Autocomplete: Codestral 22B via Continue.dev.
- Hardware: MacBook Pro M4 Pro, 48GB RAM.
- Context: 262K tokens (dense 27B, hybrid attention/Mamba, 8-bit, ~10-18 tok/s). No rate limits.
- Tool calling: qwen3_coder_xml parser.

## Constraints
- Bookmaker: Betclic. All picks conditional until user verifies in app.
- Do NOT scrape Betclic.
- Timezone: Europe/Warsaw. Betting day: 06:00–05:59. Events in progress are VALID (live betting).
- Always settle previous day before generating new picks.
- Never invent odds, lineups, injuries, results, or statistics.
- Coverage: Football, Volleyball, Basketball, Tennis, Hockey, CS2, Dota 2, Valorant.
- Statistical markets FIRST (corners, fouls, cards, shots, games, sets, frames). ML is last resort.
- No auto-rejection based on hit rates or safety scores. User decides.
- Coupon model: core portfolio + combination menu + extended pool. Core uses unique events.
- Reruns create new versions. Preserve history; mark superseded pending artifacts.
- Use `sequentialthinking` MCP for EVERY pipeline step. Per-candidate calls in S3-S7.
- Before running scripts: read code to understand data flow (inputs/outputs/keys). Never assume scripts work.

## Terminal
- Fish shell. No bash syntax, no `export`, no heredocs, no `python3 -c "..."`.
- Use `set -x VAR value` for env vars. Keep commands simple.

## Data Paths
- Output: `betting/data/`, `betting/coupons/`, `betting/reports/`, `betting/journal/`
- DB: `betting/data/betting.db`
- Stats cache: `betting/data/stats_cache/`
- Memory: `.roo/memory-bank/`
